history.text: Have you ever seen Batman Begins?
No. What is it about?
Its the origins of Batman the Dark Knight. I hate it. Well, I shouldn't say I hate it but I feel the series is super overrated.
Why do you say that?
The movie is super long. LIke, it could easily be a two part movie. I can sleep and wake up and miss nothing lol.
The actors/actresses do a great job...just holy smokes, lets get it going.
Nice lol. What actors are in it?
A lot of really good ones! Christian Bale is Batman, Katie Holmes is Rachel, Gary Oldman is the police Chief. Then you get Liam Neeson in there and Micheal Caine is Alfred. Super good line up
A few other really good actors in it too. Umm....The guy from Any Given Sunday, the sports doctor is in it...he's Two Face.

I'm happy they didn't make it into two parts because I feel that is Hollywood trying to get more cash, kinda how they did with the bow and arrow movies at the end....jlaw mockingbird...forget the name of it. Plus they did that with the last harry potters
Wow. Sounds like a good cast. Who is the director?
The director is Christopher  Nolan
Do you like super hero movies?
I do. They are some of my favorite movies. I like anything Science Fiction and Fantasy.
I love them, mainly Marvel mostly but as far as DC movies go this Batman trilogy is better than the others out. Hard to believe this came out in 05!
Ya. I like Marvel movies. The Avengers movies are great!
You'll prolly enjoy this film. I think i would have if I knew that it was so bloody long
Ya. I might need to look into that movie.
Oh man, the Avengers are so fantastic! It's great how they built those characters up to where it's like I care about what happens to them or whatever, fantastic job.
Ya. I am looking forward to more movies that Marvel might come out with.
Another thing I didn't like much about Batman trilogy was how dark it was....I know that has something to do with his persona or whatever but man, have lunch in a well lit dining room or something
I was going to say that I it sounds like a dark movie.
Does the story drag on or stay on focus?

Super dark.

I feel it drags on n on. Without giving it away any, they introduce another bad guy like half way through the movie so it's like another storyline, kinda. I didn't feel it was neccesary at all to have 2 face in there, but what do I know haha
What about the special effects?
Did they do good on the special effects?

There are some really good scenes in the movie, and I forgot to mention the Shawshank Actor, Morgan Freeman is his buddy that hooks him up with gadgets, he's great. He works at the R&D of Wayne Enterprises. There are some super cool vehicles and weapons they use for Batman
Not a whole lot in the ways of special effects, at least I don't think so, it was almost more of a drama movie than super duper action. They do some though that are pretty neat.
They go into some deep detail of how bruce wayne got skillz as a fighter/meditator. Liam neeeson actually trained him. pretty wild stuff.
I don't remember why bruce left there, dunno if liam was into some bad guy stuff or what....I think I fell asleep LOL
That sounds awesome. Is the acting good then?
Did any of the actors do their own stunts?
The acting is phenom, once I got over Batman's silly voice. The wardrobe is good and everyone loves some Katie Holmes lol
Ya. What genre would you say this movie falls into then?
I dunno about the actors doing their own stunts. I would like to think Christian Bale would, he's really really involved in his work
Definetly an action/drama superhero movie.
Nice. Sounds like a really good movie then.
It's a watcher for sure, just I don't give it hype like most places do. I'd give it a solid 6/10. I feel it was too dark and too long
OK! Thank you for telling me about it.

uid2response.feedback: The other user was able to tell me great details about the movie and answered all my questions well. The conversation went smoothly with no issues and with what he told me I want to see the movie he was talking about.
